description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for a GCP Quality Assurance Officer to work in the busy Clinical Research and Development Directorate. In this new role, the appointee will support the GCP Compliance Team in ensuring high quality research standards for ensuring compliance with the UK clinical trial regulations and the EU/GCP Directives. The post-holder, as part of the GCP Compliance Team will support the QA Manager in developing and maintaining the Quality Management System (QMS). They will also the audit function within the GCP Compliance Team in ensuring that agreed corrective and preventative actions (CAPAs) are implemented for audit findings. They will also contribute to the quality by design programme by contributing to the development of protocols for trials.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is a part time role (22.5 hours per week) available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nnedimma Okonkwo, Quality Assurance Manager, Nnedimma.Okonkwo@rmh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
